text:
the editorial proof has arrived. unfortunately i had to cancel the hardcover proof because of very lengthy delays in delivery... i suspect sinister forces at our customs & excise department. the company has kindly agreed to refund me. 
but here is the proof, and my son and i will be perusing it for areas of improvement and typos etc. i am excited - it has been a very long journey, and i think that the proof suggests that we do another round of portraits. even though this is a low budget print - the images do pop! 
thanks to the participants for their courage and patience. the book will be availed for circulation - just keep it away from eric because he loses books 😡. #africanmuse #womenofstrength #metoo #thunnderdogg #africanbeauty #fineart #nude #portraitplanet #portraiture #beauty #thisisafrica #nikonuser @hemingways_mall
name: African.Muses
tweet_full:
the editorial proof has arrived. unfortunately i had to cancel the hardcover proof because of very lengthy delays in delivery... i suspect sinister forces at our customs & excise department. the company has kindly agreed to refund me. 
but here is the proof, and my son and i will be perusing it for areas of improvement and typos etc. i am excited - it has been a very long journey, and i think that the proof suggests that we do another round of portraits. even though this is a low budget print - the images do pop!

text:
i just wanted to share some amazing news! you may or may not have heard about my documentary, but we are pretty excited about how well its doing on the festival circuit!! "documentary about akron’s own angie haze is enjoying success in festivals around the world!" akron, oh - filmmaker todd v has spent the last 3 years working closely and documenting the life of akron based singer-songwriter angie haze. out of that process he has created a very special film that chronicles not only angie’s creative process, but also the reasons behind her work. angie haze may not yet be a household name, but in her hometown, and in fact, regionally, she has made quite a name for herself in the music industry. as a multi award winning songwriter and stunning performer, she has become a perennial favorite of listeners of the summit.

this documentary digs a bit deeper into her life and creative process. in this era of the #metoo movement, we have seen how difficult yet important it is for people to speak out about their abuse, which in turn encourages other survivors to feel empowered to do the same. in this film, angie shares her own story of abuse and how it shaped the artist that she is today. it is heart wrenching and yet inspiring to see angie open up and confront her past, and create music to both aid in her healing and that of her fans. 
the film has only been on the festival circuit for a short time but has already gotten these awards:

winner - film on women - cult critic movie awards (india)
finalist - aprhodite film awards (nyc, usa)
official selection - award in inspirational films -  wrpn.tv short, tight and loose global film festival competition (delaware, usa)
official selection - gar’s garasjens film festival (norway)
official selection - wrpn women's international film festival (delaware, usa). #documentary #film #musicfilms #music #theangiehazeproject
name: The Angie Haze Project

text:
в игру "дочки-матери" играли ещё наши пра-пра-прабабушки👧👩. это игра, правила которой объяснять деткам нет необходимости. 👸девочки инстинктивно начинают играть в неё в определённом возрасте...
игра «дочки-матери» – миниатюрная модель семейных отношений👪. согласно ее сюжету, дети примеряют на себя роли родственников, как малышей, так и взрослых. если вы понаблюдаете за процессом игры, то сможете понять, как малыш видит и чувствует себя в семье😇☝. анализ психологии детской игры даст вам полезную и часто неожиданную информацию о вашем чаде👶. .
как кроха понимает требования и запреты в семье? с кем из родственников он себя ассоциирует? чем для него являются семейные отношения?👪
👀"подсмотрите" за вашим ребенком в процессе игры.  отмечайте важные детали: кого играет ваша дочь? какие манеры этого родственника она копирует? если это один из родителей, то как он относится к ребенку? что поощряет, а что запрещает и как? повышает ли голос на куклу-ребенка? за что хвалит? .
наблюдения за игрой в дочки-матери позволит вам увидеть отношения с ребенком со стороны👧👩. конечно, реальные факты в таком «зеркале» искажены детским восприятием, но основная идея прослеживается👍. .
классическая сплюшка-мама, мини версия- её дочка, закажите обе куколки и играйте с удовольствием🤗💖
.
сплюшка классик 890₽
сплюшка мини 550₽
.
p.s. на фото ночник котёнок гав от наших друзей @babayki_net .

text:
equilibrio. una palabra linda. 
una meta a veces difícil de sostener.
te cuento que cuando a mi me pasó, las que habían sido mis amigas "de la infancia", "del colegio", no me creyeron. 
no me lo dijeron en la cara, pero una de ellas, con hijos, incluso, uno de esos hijos es mujer y ya casi mayor de edad por entonces. esa mujer no sorora, lo habló en una reunión de esas de "reencuentro escolar", a la que yo no había ido. está ex amiguita dijo: "seguro que es mentira, debe ser con alguien que salió y se enojó" ... mis amigas no preguntaron. tampoco se acercaron a mi, como si contagiara, ni me preguntaron nada. 
los chicos, sí, los hombres compañeros de infancia se acercaron. 
por otro lado, gente curiosa, que preguntaban la parte del morbo, de los detalles. ¿para qué?  si no eran ni abogad@s ni iban a salir en mi defensa...
pasé de ell@s... caí en algunas "profesionales de la salud" como una psicóloga que me grabó el audio de la sesión con lujo de detalles ... y cuando se lo pedí para el juicio no  me lo quiso dar.

una guionista que lo único que pretendía era tener datos para escribir al respecto, quizás con realismo.

los de siempre con un '¿cómo no te defendiste?' ... me dolió y mucho que esas mujeres de 40 años que eran amigas desde niñas, pasaron a ser... punzantes espinas. 
primero me contaron lo que una de ellas había dicho,dos de los chicos y después,un año después  se acercaron 3 mujeres de diferentes edades pidiéndome  perdón por haberles creído a ésta hoy ex amiga a-sorora
que feo, triste y fuerte, además de lo que te pasó...tener que escuchar esos agravios.
esta ilustración, representa mi deseo éste #2019.
 el caso mío, sucedió en #2015 y éramos 3 mujeres abrazadas. mi madre, ceci (madre de mis sobrinos nietos) y yo.

en #2018 fuimos más. pero aún se critican  entre mujeres...minas que hablan de "lo pura que es tal o cual". deseo que nos multipliquemos en amor, verdad y sonrisas + sanación comunitaria. 
se puede. .
.
#diariodeunamujerviolada #bastaparami #wearefamily #somosuno #nosotras #yo #ella #ustedes #mujeres #mujer #niña #chicas #adolescentes #girls #woman #women #together #us #you #them #me #yo #metoo #yotambien #sororidad #2019 #justicia

dear @ladygaga , what ever media and other people say, you are a good human and everybody makes mistakes. i cried last night so much because everyone is so nasty to you and it’s breaking my heart. i have to admit that i was a little bit confused this situation but i’ll always stand by you because you also stood by me when i needed you most. i know that you feel so bad right now but honey i believe in you and in your apology. i love you.

she has never said that she hadn't known about the accusations about r. kelly. or that it was the first time she heard about it after the surviving r. kelly document. people twist her words and i'm disappointed that all the blame is on gaga. there is so many other people too that have worked with r. kelly during this whole mess. why they're not being blamed as bad as gaga is? it is very unfortunate that it's been so many years and just now we all have opened our eyes to this and see who r. kelly really is. i live in finland and i'm trying to keep up with the news about music industry, but i have to admit that yesterday was the first time i heard about this case. about these accusations of r. kelly being in sexcult and about the pedophilia. the first accusations have been around from year 2000. i did hear some rumours about some rapper being in sexcult but i just thought it was some passing scandal. it really was not. if you really think about it, we are all to blame, because whe have listened to his songs and went to his gigs. so stop throwing hate towards gaga or anyone else who have worked with r. kelly and start looking in the mirror. r. kelly himself is the only one to blame. 
peace.

text:
goodmorning saints! god says: come out of your tomb! lazarus was dead in his tomb but jesus saw fit to resurrect him from the dead! a lot of us need to be resurrected from time to time because of the things going on in our lives. a big part of being resurrected is being unbound from our emotional state of being. first thing we have to do is answer the call from jesus to come out of our tombs! the bible says: “when he had said these things, he cried out with a loud voice, “lazarus, come out." the man who had died came out, his hands and feet bound with linen strips, and his face wrapped with a cloth. jesus said to them, “unbind him, and let him go.” john‬ ‭11:43-44‬ ‭esv‬‬. jesus called to lazarus and told him to come out and he walked out! remember jesus will call but it's up to you to come out! and once you come out jesus will unbind you! letting go of pain, hurt and anger with forgiveness in your heart is key once you are out of your tomb! the bible also says: "let all bitterness and wrath and anger and clamor and slander be put away from you, along with all malice. be kind to one another, tenderhearted, forgiving one another, as god in christ forgave you. ”ephesians‬ ‭4:31-32‬ ‭esv‬‬. also remember the things that are binding you can cause you to sin! so answer the call! come out of your tomb! and allow god to free you from bondage! amen!! i love you all with the love of jesus christ! stay blessed and faithful!

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text: “women from all across the globe have raised their hands and used the #metoo hashtag,” @lisa_borders, the first president and ceo of @timesupnow, says in our february issue. “they want to move from a place of survivorship to empowerment. they’re saying, ‘i have my own personal power; now let’s make that a collective power.’” and much of that is thanks to time’s up. for those who think the organization is little more than a hollywood fad, think again — they’re entering their second year and 3,500 people have reached out to them. 60 cases are underway, ranging from cashier at a dollar store in brooklyn to paramedics in chicago. click the link in bio to read about how @lisa_borders is turning the organization into way more than a movement. #instylebadasswomen i photographed by @jeremy_liebman

text:
the death of a lie #113 - victim shaming will continue to silence women & girls. statements like if you really got raped you would have...... are insensitive, inhumane and detached.  although every situation is different rape is not different,  it is rape. especially to the person who experienced it. 
deciding someone's value based on their clothing, body type, sexual history, personality or age is the very thing that allows women to continue to be preyed upon.  these ideals continue to promote the dehumanization of black girls and black women. 
assuming that a child has the capacity to think like an adult is asinine.  assuming that a broken child who has been exposed to sexual experiences could not grow up to be a broken woman is asinine.  blaming a child for not being able to protect themselves from predators in which their parents or guardians exposed them to or were unaware of is asinine. assuming that most women want to publicly disclose anything about their sexual history, especially something that will allow others to judge and berate them and then attempt to guesstimate their worth or value is ridiculous.

silence is not consent or approval.  and, we have the audacity to wonder why women wait such a long time to come out with their stories.. smh

text:
#metoo #metoomovement 
as a survivor please know this... it isn't easy to heal from. for the rest of your life you will have to live with the abuse and the remainder of what happened. 
but know this. you can still have a happy life. you don't have to let that make you a bad person. you don't have to be a victim all your life. i was a little girl when my innocent was taken. by people who i didn't know. in the foster care system people do a lot of stuff that gets overlooked. i've dealt with domestic violence.. something i live with on a daily basis. 
just know you will survive...💯💪 you don't have to let what happened to you continue to rent space in your head or your heart any longer. yes it's hard to forget. and you probably won't ever be able to forget about it. but you can love and live without remaining a victim to the things that has happened.

message approved by a rape and domestic violence survivor 💯💪

text:
yesterday was a pretty big shit show. 😂⁣
⁣
3 days away from my year of sobriety anniversary and i’m processing and healing so many thoughts around it and the last 34 almost 35 years of my life. ⁣
⁣
it’s crazy how much pain you have to walk through when you are healing old unconscious ways of living. you actually have to come face to face with the stuff you tried numbing for so long. (in my case a lifetime) ⁣
⁣
this soul work is not for the faint of heart. it’s hard. it’s challenging. it’s sometimes physically painful. but everyday it is worth it. ⁣
⁣
as i watched the sun start to go down on the beach last night, i stood there with the light beaming onto my face and i asked god and the enlightened archangels to keep facilitating this healing, no matter how hard it is. i could handle it. i wanted it! ⁣
⁣
you see, this upcoming celebration of a year of sobriety is so much more than healing a decade of abusing alcohol...it’s about healing at a soul level for this life and the ones before it. deep deep soul work that i crave more than i used to crave wine. 🙃⁣
⁣
if you’re healing things and it feels like a complete mess...keep going. there will be light at the end. just keep going. ⁣
💞✨🙏🏻⁣
⁣
⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

text: "man box culture also suppresses empathy. the suppression of boys’ and men’s empathy is no accident. it is the suppression of empathy that makes a culture of ruthless competition, bullying and codified inequality possible. it is in the absence of empathy that men fail to see women’s equality and many other social issues for what they are: simple and easily enacted moral imperatives. instead, our sons buy into bullying and abuse as central mechanisms for forming and expressing male status and identity." mark greene, @remakingmanhood | the little #metoo book for men

text: i always find it strange when women oppose the feminist movement - women who read, women who vote, women who have their own credit cards and can apply for their own mortgage, women who went to college, women who have jobs, women who chose when they were ready to be pregnant, and women who married for love. it seems contradictory for a woman to be anti-feminism while also living the life with all the freedoms that the feminist movement fought for. if you’re anti-feminism, does that also mean that you’re ok with going back to the way things were? i’ve often wondered if maybe they’re anti-feminism because they want to protect the honor of the men in their lives. does the empowerment of women threaten the honor of a man? sure there are extremists that are man-haters, but just like in any movement, the extremists get attention but they don’t represent the whole. it isn’t about reducing the value of a man, it’s about proving that women are of equal value. women, stop putting down other women - the obstacles you put in their path will inevitably be in yours. supreme court justice ruth ginsburg said, "women's rights are an essential part of the overall human rights agenda, trained on the equal dignity and ability to live in freedom all people should enjoy." feminism isn’t about taking away the rights or honor of a man, instead it’s about offering the same rights and honor to both genders.

text:
полиция лас-вегаса запросила образцы днк криштиану роналду, которого в изнасиловании обвинила бывшая американская модель кэтрин майорга.

происшествие, о котором идет речь, случилось еще в 2009 году. по словам женщины, известный футболист набросился на нее в гостиничном номере при одном из казино лас-вегаса, где они познакомились за несколько часов до этого. тогда майорга сразу же обратилась в полицию, но, как утверждают американские сми, позже согласилась уладить дело без суда и за свое молчание якобы получила 375 тыс. долларов.

однако в октябре 2018 года, на фоне движения #metoo, женщина решила вновь подать жалобу в полицию. в ответ роналду написал в "твиттере", что разбирательства он не боится и что его совесть чиста. одновременно он заявил, что комментарии в сми делать не намерен, чтобы избежать ненужных спекуляций.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

there is a lot of different stuff that says " only two! " 
or " more then two!!" i feel we don't know enough to say which is which. because if you say " no this " another 12  things will just come out saying " no two!!" or " no more then two!!" so i feel its more complicated then a yes or  no answer. 
the human mind is so big and strange it  could do basically anything if it wanted  but also completely mess you up real bad. 
i know theres two sexes but i think there are more then two genders. 
to say there's only man and woman doesn't make much sense to me because what makes a man? what makes a woman gender wise not sex wise so is it just saying " i feel like a man/woman!" so why can't it be that way for those who are on the trans spectrum? 
to me two gender identities don't make sense when people have talked about feeling so many different things sincerely from their hearts. ~ witchy

text:
you are reckless, selfish, stubborn sometimes rude.
you've bottled up the pain of so much that has been done.
when you're hurt you close into yourself, shut down.
you love attention and yet love being by yourself more.
may god have mercy on your soul for you are truly lost.
daily you fight your demons yet no one knows of that which you endure.
you bear it alone, never speaking of it.
you can blame the broken home from which you came or the environment that you grew up in.
the people who tore you down so young.
you can point the finger at those who have whispered behind your back.
they all have played a role in your development.
but looking so deep into the past will keep you from moving forward.
you must love yourself more than these people claim they do.
look at where you stand now. 🌹

text:
[1.3] #fbf | award season kicked off last sunday with the @goldenglobes. while nowadays walking the red carpet at the lustrous beverly hilton has become just another excuse to show off – and try to establish –one’s status and glamour power (missing out on such a gala is absolutely not an option!), back in marilyn’s days actresses and actors were much less mainstream. indeed actors were rebels: awards played no role in increasing their cachet, they were perceived as stars solely because they had talent and made the audience dream. 
_______________

1952: marilyn monroe receives the henrietta trophy as best young box office personality at the world film favorite festival (which would later become the golden globe awards as we know them). she’s just approaching stardom, and wearing a passionately red strapless dress with the meekness and shyness she was known for.

text:
już jutro w wo:
- gdy się złości, nie wstydzi się tego, nie przeprasza. jest wszędzie tam, gdzie się jej nie spodziewają. robi rzeczy, których kobiecie rzekomo "nie wypada" robić: siada na drodze neonazistów z marszu niepodległości czy maluje sprayem drzwi biura posła pis - rozmową kasi wężyk z psycholożką elżbietą podleśną otwieramy najnowszy numer.

w nim ponadto: - kino. sandra bullock: po #metoo mężczyźni stali się uważni na to, co mówią i jak się do nas zwracają - zdrowie. clair wineland, przez 21 lat chorowała na mukowiscydozę: żyjemy w świecie, który czerpie korzyści z naszego dążenia do szczęścia. wystarczy, że powiemy: nie, nie będziemy szukać szczęścia, jesteśmy żywi i to nam wystarczy, i obalimy system - natalia de barbaro: przeszkadza ci manspreading? przytrzymaj chwilę dłużej swój łokieć na podłokietniku fotela - sztuczna inteligencja. roboty to algorytmy. jeśli kobiet zabraknie przy ich tworzeniu, świat przyszłości będzie męski - disign. musimy budować domy, które uciekną przed tsunami, czy huraganem - a także najlepsze bajgle w kuchni, zapachy, które dodadzą nam energii, a w męskiej końcówce piotr głuchowski o zapiekłości na kler.

poleca redaktorka naczelna,
aleksandra klich 
#sobotazobcasami #wysokieobcasy #kobietywiedzącorobią #samodobro @gazeta_wyborcza

text:
i am a survivor of sexual abuse and a huge advocate for the #metoo revolution. this is why i’m stepping away from my usual content to help bring awareness to this horrible and disgusting crime.
🤬
being female is difficult, not just in america but all over the world. no young girl says to herself “when i grow up i want to be a prostitute.” they are forced into it. the how doesn’t matter as it’s not like a choice is given.
🚫
the best way to end human trafficking is to get rid of the traffickers. in order to do that, more effective laws need to be in place and many states have a ways to go in fighting this on a state level. the trafficking victims protection act was authorized in 2000 and was the first federal law to address sex trafficking in the united states. it was reauthorized in 2003, 2005, and 2008 but expired in 2011.
⚖️
we currently have a president who has very little regard for women or children so it’s imperative we fight for more stricter laws on a state level so the federal law can be updated. the patriarchy must end!
.
.
.
.
#nationalhumantraffickingawarenessday #humantrafficking #sextrafficking #humanrights #womensrights #stoptheviolence #smashthepatriarchy #enoughisenough #protectourchildren #protectwomen #protectgirls

text:
2/26 weeks of feminism. this week i asked @clairebresnan her thoughts on her meaning of feminism and why she needs it. 
she said this: “i’m often afraid to draw attention to the ways gender inequality has impacted my life because i don’t want to underscore my privilege or portray myself as a victim. however, i do see the ways society’s expectations of women have seeped into my relationships and self image. only once we acknowledge inequality can we address it. it’s our responsibility to color in the grey space by normalizing and putting words to our shared experience. i’m ready to replace “it could have been worse” with “it shouldn’t have happened” and recognize the ways i’m affected. i wish i could refuse to walk the streets in fear, but a serial rapist has broken into my house. i wish i could trust fully, but my teammates and i were groomed as potential victims by my youth climbing coach and didn’t see it until several people i care about were abused. i wish i could embrace my femininity, but when i do it’s met with a marked increase in unwanted advances. i wish i could open up more to my male acquaintances, but it’s always been portrayed as my responsibility to not lead people on or come across as needy. i need feminism because striving for a better world is not the same as complaining, and though my problems are small compared to much of the world, they should not be invisible.” #feminism #feminist #26weeksoffeminism #crankyfeminist #whatdoesfeminismmeantoyou #femme #timesup #metoo #weneedfeminism #patriarchysucksbecause #equality

text:
you can: make an effort even when you don't want to. .
you can: choose not to fight
.
you can:  not allow someone the opportunity to re-write your history .
you can: do nothing. .
having a disagreement with someone you love is hard. especially when you realize how wrong they really are and that they will never acknowledge that or give you any closure. .
so i sit with that.  and then move on, realizing my emotions and my moments are mine to define. .
as someone that is still coming to terms with the sexual abuse i endured as a child by a predatory neighbor....i have to constantly remind myself that it was not my fault. that there is no blame for 11 year old lacye. not telling and "allowing" it to happen does not make that my burden. or my crime. .

text:
somatic practice short course, 2019
university of bedfordshire 
the somatic practice short course is aimed at dance practitioners, teachers, community dance artists and graduate level students.  the course explores contemporary issues in somatic practices with lots of opportunity to dance, explore and engage in experiential enquiry of the body mind. £60/£50 for part 1, 2, or 3. £140/£110 for parts 1, 2 and 3 booked together. 
booking: tamara.ashley@beds.ac.uk 
somatic practice short course part 1: contact improvisation and the somatics of touch
with tamara ashley

this course runs on wednesdays from 10-1 from 20 february to 27 march.

somatic practices offer a range of tactile tools that can enhance our practice of contact improvisation. touch and tactile learning can offer intuitive, felt and sensitive facets to our dancing. hands on work, and tactile tools can enable dancers to access different systems, alignments and feeling states in the body mind.  in this part of the course, there will be specific focus on touch and facilitation techniques.

in the context of consent, trauma, participatory questions and #metoo, we will look at systematic ways of approaching touch in terms of pedagogy, permission and performance.  personal somatic inquiry will be supported and encouraged through discussion, writing, journaling and reflection. 
we will explore touch and tactile dimensions of our dancing through dancing, watching and assisting one another. there will be lots of dancing! 
somatic practice short course part 2: contact improvisation and the art of relating
with anna jussilainen 
30 april – 4 may 
an in depth investigation of the art of touch in contact improvisation.  #somatics #dance #touch #contactimprovisation
name: Tamara Ashley

text:
good morning my beautiful kings and queens

one thing i can factually say is sexual abuse doesnt have a name, a race, a certain job, a sex, etc. it attacks anyone at anytime. look at him. you would never know by his business attire and handsomness. 
meet my king cortland jones who was sexual assaulted by a family member at the tender age of 4. i need you to understand how someones life is stripped away from them by someone elses choice. how do you expect someone to grow up and be normal?

courtlands journey wasnt easy until he met god. 
please welcome and give cortland some words of love and growth as he continues on his journey to happiness. his book, "out of darkness" shares how he is overcoming his abuse. 
cortland, my king, thank you for your bravery. sharing your truth to the world is a huge step towards healing and i commend you. i love you and stay on your journey. we are in this together. 
men hurt too. open your eyes people. this is real

dont be afraid to share your truth. free yourself from this darkness my kings and queens 
i love you and remember stay beautiful
#thebeautifulmovement
#sexualabuse#abuse#sex#movement#king#queen#advocate#journey#family#hurt#abuse#metoo#iloveyou#hurtpeoplehurtpeople

text:
"panty portrait: twat" from the panty project,12 of 51
.

fiber art, archival pigment print on museum cotton rag, 19 x 14 inches .
the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.

text:
#mythoughts #anotherone

i’m seriously having a hard time listening to people defend rkelly just bc he’s who he has always been. so? i haven’t purposely listened to him since 2002. don’t separate him from his art. his art is literally a journal of his crimes. 
this is why i said nothing after that girl laughed at me about my rape, saying why would my cousin do that? #retraumatized. i shut up for 10 years. had his baby and all. even allowed him to touch me again bc, hey, nobody believed me. 🤷🏽‍♀️ so he’s still walking around free. he even had the audacity to approach me at family functions talking about why i brought my boyfriend when i knew how he felt about me. #sick 
i have no idea how many more he’s done that to after me but i do know of one before me. we share a similar story except i became a mom from it. so she didn’t speak up and stop it from happening to me and i didn’t stop it from happening to anyone else. i carry that guilt around. it’s now my mission to share and help as many people as i can. 
with statistics like 1 in 4 girls going through assault before 18 (and 1 in 6 guys), someone else on your timeline is being retraumatized by your, “but he makes good music”. #disgusted 😒

so, if you still support that man, do those of us survivors out there a favor and keep it to yourself. 
i’ve already unfollowed a few people bc i can’t take seeing their support of him. .
.
.

text:
this was a very hard poem to write because it evoked too many emotions. special thanks to @gurjot.s.kaler -  full video is out now. plz watch and share the link below.👍 https://youtu.be/ffndfsmmrve 🙏

the poem, this  happens  with  every  girl : "me - too'' by gurjot s. kaler ,
is a heartfelt tribute to the millions of women in the world who suffer in  silence and are a victim of sexual harassment-cum-exploitation at every stage of their lives. indeed, it is actually a heartrending reality and a matter of grave concern to note that everyday,  innumerable women are raped, molested, eve-teased and sexually assaulted across the globe. 
the tragic truth is that every women has undergone the pain of sexual violence and faced some sort of sexual abuse during their lifetime, either directly or indirectly. 
the question which really begs for an answer is that whenever any kind of sexual crime happens with women, why are we all silent as the members of society ? don't we all have any moral and social responsibility to stand upright and defend our women's honor, prestige and integrity ? 
why do we refuse to raise our voice ? are we also waiting for that one day when our own mothers, sisters, wives and daughters will come home after becoming victims of sexual harassment and say that, "this happened with me-too". do not suffer in silence. raise your voice before it is too late. the world suffers a lot, not because of the violence of bad people but because of the silence of good people. be the change you wish to see in the world. 
the time has come to realize that we must gather the required courage to support, respect and protect our women as well as ensure their safety, security and survival at any cost.  therefore, "me-too'' is not a mere hashtag, its a global movement in support of women and is meant to  inspire them to raise their suppressed voices against all sorts of injustice in society. 
respect her - support her - protect her.

https://www.facebook.com/gurjot.s.kaler

https://www.instagram.com/gurjot.s.kaler

#metoo #metoomovement #gurjotskaler #gurjotkaler #respectwomen #womenempowerment - #regrann

text:
too many women hold back from sharing their writing with the world because: -
a) they don’t feel good enough.
-
b they question whether anyone would want to hear what they have to share.
-
c) writing a book feels far too overwhelming and time-consuming.
-
no more! -
the time for holding back has passed. -
movements such as #metoo have shown us the power of women coming together and sharing their stories. and if there’s one thing we’re certain of, it’s that in these tumultuous and transformational times, the world needs your magic. -
at the unbound press we honour the right of every woman to be her fullest, freest self and to write in a way that expresses that. and we’re creating a magical community of authors who are coming together to change the world, one book at a time. -
are you with us?

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
for the first time in its 127-year history, the apa has issued guidelines to help psychologists specifically address the issues of men and boys.
.
.
.
according to the american psychological association, “the new “guidelines for the psychological practice with boys and men” defines “masculinity ideology” as “a particular constellation of standards that have held sway over large segments of the population, including: anti-femininity, achievement, eschewal of the appearance of weakness, and adventure, risk, and violence.” the report also links this ideology to homophobia, bullying and sexual harassment.”
.
.
.
“men commit approximately 90 percent of all homicides in the u.s., they are far more likely than women to be arrested and charged with intimate partner violence in the u.s., and they are four times more likely than women to die of suicide worldwide.”
.
.
.

text:
i've lived for most of my adult life on intentional communities, where essential resources, dreams, and power are all shared, to some capacity, among a group of people.  during this time, but especially in the last five years, i often found myself in the role of creating organizational structures for self governance and decision making. .

to do this, i had to learn how to ask what peoples' feelings and behaviors revealed about how we structured ourselves as a group, and try to shift those structures to affect people's future behaviors.  it was like living inside a dynamic puzzle, with all the pieces and all the outcomes growing and changing over time. .

there are lots of changes that we made that i'm proud of; there were also lots of failures that still confound me.  but as i exit the ranch community, i find that those failures are becoming my biggest tools for learning.  not just the how or the why or the what, but the fact of it:  there were certain things i failed to change, despite every ounce of my most tenacious efforts.  why? .

the podcast on being with rebecca traister and avi klein--#metoo through a solutions lense, hit me hard yesterday, because i think it speaks to a lot of the central issues we faced as a community, and to many of the reasons why our issues with gender inequality were so hard to change.  it was so emotionally challenging to dismantle structures of gender inequality from within relationships that were of paramount importance to all of us.  we learned how to talk about it, but not how to do it.  and this underlying reality was revealed in the patterns of behavior that repeated themselves over and over again, despite all our best words to the contrary.  i think this podcast is spot on in exploring the nature of the emotional challenges men and women face as we push for real vs performative feminism, and also some incredible perspectives for overcoming those challenges.

to do this, i had to learn how to ask what peoples' feelings and behaviors revealed about how we structured ourselves as a group, and try to shift those structures to affect people's future behaviors.  it was like living inside a dynamic puzzle, with all the pieces and all the outcomes growing and changing over time. .

text: i am so inspired by everyone's comments, messages, and stories. when i first started talking to people about starting this business, they worried that i'd be dragged down or emotionally drained by others' stories. nope, quite the opposite. yes, i have sympathy and empathy for you because i've been there and i am still putting in the work every single day, but i can tell you with full confidence that i am not disheartened, mad, or saddened by any of the things your share. i have faith, love, and confidence in your growth potential. i know you can transform the suckiest part of your journey into your biggest strength. i believe in every single person that has seen the darkness and continues to put one foot in front of the other and i also believe in the good in humanity for those that are on here to learn how to support someone through their trauma. thank you for sharing your stories with me. let's continue to grow together!

text:
trigger warning: sexual harassment 💔💔💔
i was 9 when i first met him, i was really happy to be honest because my previous molvi was too strict and he used to hit me for my mistakes. he was nicer and better at teaching me the quran, and i wouldn’t have imagined in my worst of dreams he could turn out this way.
the first few days, maybe months were good, he was a nice person, at least that what my 9 year old self thought, he used to make jokes too aside from teaching me maybe which is why we bonded in a way, i was a child, i didn’t know what was right or wrong. but as months passed, he started touching me in places i didn’t feel nice. he used to keep his hand too high on my thigh when i used to recite the quran to him, he used to make me sit on his lap, and i didn’t know how to ask him to stop. i was too silent. i didn’t know what it meant or what it was. 
7 years, he went on for 7 years everyday touching me inappropriately and i couldn’t stop it, i kept shut, it still haunts me and scares me. and the irony of him having two girls, i don’t wish bad on that at all, never can, i would never want any girl going through this but oh god if only he thought about his little girls before doing this to me. 
i still shiver and cry whenever i think of it, i wish i could’ve stopped it some way but i used to go numb and silent. why is it that he who taught me islam and the words of god turned worse than a devil. 
i still haven’t opened up to my parents about it, i don’t know how to. it wasn’t long back when i realized what was happening to me but i was too ashamed, i guess. and now it only cuts deeper every time i think of it.
i do see him sometimes, very rarely. but i prefer hiding myself somewhere instead. 
i cant face him anymore. the memories just open up in front of me like an open book and i see everything flash by. i don’t think i can ever heal over this. i just cant.
#metoo

text:
i’m excited to share my newest (and extremely vulnerable) podcast interview with the amazing @katiehorwitch on @womenagainstnegativetalk !! to say this conversation was intense & powerful would be an understatement. i talk about trudging through pain rather than moving around it, why i’ve forgiven and have empathy for the man who brutally raped and beat me, why we silence our suffering, how to view your adversity as an opportunity in your life rather than an opposition, and so much more. we went all in...and then some.
•
feeling so so grateful to this community of women who continue to offer me space to show up, bare my truth, and inspire others to take brave action in their own lives. grab a box of tissues (trust me you’ll need them), give it a listen...and let me know what you think.
•
link in bio. also available on apple podcasts and spotify, just search for want: women against negative talk.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
so i really don’t like comparing the us to france because it’s cliché and both cultures have so much to offer. *but* we can learn from each other and here’s something we can learn from my french peeps.
.
france has an actual branch of government dedicated to equality between men and women. its minister is marlene schiappa and she is a powerful voice and protector of gender equality. france created a government branch dedicated to the rights of women back in 1974 (by the same president who called my dear simone veil to become the minister of health). this would be a dream here in the us t have a government branch solely dedicated to women’s rights. i’m willing to be many men would have more incentive to behave.
.
this is what philofem is about. .
.
madame schiappa, merci pour votre travail et votre mission. @marleneschiappa

today, january 11 is national human trafficking awareness day. with over 40 million slaves in the world today, human trafficking is one of the greatest injustices of our lifetime. @lovejusticeintl attacks human trafficking at the most strategic point: while a person is being trafficked and sends them to safety, while at the same time gathering data and arresting and convicting traffickers. you can help save a life for just $100, or less than $10 a month. every life is beautiful and worth fighting for. visit link in bio (lovejustice.ngo) to learn more.

text:
announcement

we have teamed up with a small states owned enterprise to produce a limited run of chop sticks with our little tiny tadpole sized big beautiful cranes (#bbc) sprayed all over from the tip and running down the shaft all the way to where the hand grips it firmly.

these limited edition chop sticks could also be used to hold up your man bun and yes they come in pink too. 
so the deal is we are now brand ambassadors for georgia chop stick, thus a 10% percent from each set sold with our offer code #longshaftbbc10 will go straight to environmental remediation in china particularly in heavy crane density zones.

there are only 100,000 sets made and they are strictly available in kitchen stores worldwide as as well as online and oriental grocery stores. this agreement could raise up to 1,200 yuan for the cranes. its not much but we will take anything for the cranes! go out there and #creaseforpeace bird lovers!

#fighttheman #metoo #endtheextinction #earthtoo #cranestoo #lgbqtc @peta @seashepherd #christmas #origami #vegetablepower #vegetable #vegancat #veganleopard #flatearth #spheroidalearth #deliciousvegfood #vegetablepowered #armtheanimals #getsomeporkbetweenyoursticks #crueltyfree #greenhousegas #climatechange #migratefortheclimate #chopstick #chopsuey #tofustirfry #collaborate #childlaborfree

text:
this is my dog, kratos. i rescued him from a life of abuse when he was 6 months old but he recused me everytime i faced abuse of my own. there were times i was so depressed i didn't want to live and feel pain anymore but my dog saved me from myself. if i was gone, who would take care of my baby? he gave me a reason to stay. that's why i wanted to create this foundation because animals have a way of helping us heal, and in return, we can help them heal as well. that's why i want to create a dv shelter that accepts animals because you need your biggest support in your biggest time of need💜🐾
.
.
.

•
in celebration of the 25th anniversary of nasa's first space servicing mission to the hubble space telescope, we are sharing this gallery of images from all five of the hubble servicing missions.
🛰
astronauts serviced hubble for the first time in december 1993. including that trip, there have been five astronaut servicing missions to hubble between 1993 and 2009.
🚀
astronaut steven l. smith, payload commander, retrieves a power tool while standing on the mobile foot restraint at the end of the remote manipulator system (rms). many of the tools required to service the hubble space telescope are stored on the handrail attached to the rms visible in the photograph.
✨

i am excited to officially announce one of the panelist for f fear book launch event,  domestic violence expert & founder of @thestillstandingalliance, tamiko lowry pugh @tamikolowrypugh 🎉🎉🎉
•
tamiko lowry pugh often referred to as "the empowering diva" is a voice for women's empowerment. as the ceo of empowerme! life coaching & consulting - a personal development & lifestyle enhancement firm for women and the founder of the still standing alliance – a nonprofit organization that that focuses on domestic violence awareness, advocacy, and prevention, she has constructed a powerful movement dedicated to the empowerment and personal development of women across the world. after hearing this panel, you will leave empowered and enlightened with practical tips to better protect yourself and loved ones in the future. we are celebrating solutions!💪
•
🔴rsvp today!🙋🏾‍♀️

please rsvp, seating is limited. 📖 you can pre-order your book with your rsvp. •

text:
why can’t men be taught not to rape ? 
we’re taught from a young age that we should dress “decently” so that we don’t arouse our fathers and uncles 
but why can’t men be taught from a young age to be aroused by our personalities i.e. humor and other traits .
it’s really sad and pathetic how the decency to not rape is overshadowed by how we should be responsible enough to avoid getting raped .

text: imagine that you are a rape victim. maybe you once sent drunken texts to a friend about your favourite sexual positions or exchanged nude photos with a previous boyfriend. if it’s on your mobile, the police will look at it. if they think there’s a remote chance that it might be relevant, they will have to show it to prosecutors and disclose it to the defence – and there’s every chance you will be questioned about it in court. the survivor knows that you or society blames her for the abuse, s/he will not feel safe or comfortable coming forward and talking to you. victim-blaming attitudes also reinforce what the abuser has been saying all along; that it is the victim’s fault this is happening. it is not the victim’s fault or responsibility to fix the situation; it is the abuser’s choice. by engaging in victim-blaming attitudes, society allows the abuser to perpetrate relationship abuse or sexual assault while avoiding accountability for his/her actions.... #rapevictim #rapist #rape #hearmetoo #consent #abuse #metoo #womanempowerment #humanrights #feminism #survivingrkelly #sexualabuse #sexualviolence #sexualassault #rapevictim #rapeculture #feminist #love #anime #women #sex #domesticviolence #woman #nomore #survivor

text:
[1/5] “as 2018 has ended i have had a moment to reflect, i look back and see this past year as one of major ups and downs. running your own business is hard work - it requires commitment, grit, and resilience. not only am i carrying the weight of continuing to make it on my own, but i also have scars from a traumatic childhood that i have to breathe around every single day. in early 2017, i saw the #metoo movement gain momentum around me as many women came out and spoke about their experiences with sexual assault. it was then when one of my deepest truths, the fact that i had been molested as a child by a relative, started to be relived within the walls of my mind. i remember thinking to myself, “you can actually speak about this?” i come from a community of south asian immigrants that abides by a “sweep under the f*ckin rug” culture that made my speaking out more prolonged than it needed to be. i spent my childhood swallowed by my own silence and my inability to feel safe in telling anyone about my experience. the inspiration that the #metoo movement ignited in me let me know that my time to finally speak my truth was near and i collaborated with @browngirlmag and @sakhinyc to put together a panel of south asian women to share their stories of surviving sexual assault. the event took place in march of 2018 and was a success, i felt freer than i have ever felt before. being in a room full of other women who were fellow survivors gave me the sense of connection i was missing as a child. one of my goals in 2019 is to keep the trend of openness going with my friends and followers. the more i can share with you all about my experiences, the more i can impact lives and spark change around an issue that we have just skimmed the surface in talking about. recently, i stumbled upon a set of posts from @wendyslookbook that have pushed me to tell my story in more detail and to describe my journey as a survivor. drawing inspiration from wendy, i have come together with my team to create a narrative that best describes what i went through. this is my story, #metoo.”🙏🏽
-
to read all 5️⃣ parts of karuna chani's story, visit her page @karunachani.
-
📸 @tarasharma
✍🏼 @pri_pards

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

محكمه منحت الممثل #الوك_ناث خروج بكفالة من قضية الاغتصاب .
مُنِح الممثل المخضرم الوك ناث كفالة استباقية من قبل محكمة دندوشي يوم السبت في قضية اغتصاب رفعتها كاتبه السيناريو فينتا ناندا. الشهر الماضي ، قدم ناث طلبًا بكفالة أمام المحكمة ، بعد شهر من قيام شرطة أوشيوارا بحجزه بسبب اتهامه بالاغتصاب. مع اكتساب حركة #metoo العالمية زخما في الهند ، قامت فينتا ناندا ، من حسابه على الفيسبوك بتاريخ 8 أكتوبر 2018 ، بتفصيل محنتها من تعرضها للاغتصاب من قبل الوك ناث خلال مسلسل التلفزيوني تارا ، الذي كانت تنتجه وتكتبه في ذلك الوقت.
وكتبت ناندا أنها تعرضت للاعتداء الجنسي أكثر من مرة من قبل ناث بعدها تم أزلت اسمه من مسلسل التلفزيوني لسوء التصرف مع الممثلة المشارك معه نافنيت نيشان.
( بس حصلت معلومات عن مسلسل لقيت اسمه موجود 🤔 المهم ما علينا انا منصدمه منه )
.
.
.
कादर खान ने आराम करने के लिए, टोरंटो में दफन किया .
.
.

thank you for processing your emotions, easing your own pain and fulfilling your own external and internal needs- so when we meet, which we will, alchemy is made.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
writing heals

when i started to write in my first journal i sincerely didn't think i'd get much out of it.. fast forward a decade and i have one of the most effective self-help tools for healing 📓🙌 it is such a great way to organise your thoughts, work through trauma and honestly express your feelings in a sincere,  non-judgemental way.

no-one else reads it so often you feel free to write things that you might never say or are too scared to say in real life! 
do something nice for yourself this weekend and buy yourself a new journal.. it can be the next step on your road to recovery!
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: in this past week ive grown tired of the collective sigh of outrage from black women whom are reacting to the rkelly docuseries. soooo... yep! i am saying it! in general, black women do not (initially) support other women who identify themselves as victims of harassment of men. period. instead, women of color would rather portray said victim as malevolent and vindictive and will go so far as to make enough statements against that woman who told her truth story, to ensure that not only is her #truth not a truth at all but that that particular ‘victim’ doesn’t jibe with the manufactured version of the ‘strong-black-woman’ narrative. this conjured trace of us is designed to be held as an esteem for prominent women of our identity and socialization as the world should allegedly see it. we'd tear our sister down and puposely choke her with her hurt before we embrace her with empathy and hold her up as she goes through. ha! i speak from experience. btw, this is how rkelly was able to get away with the mess he is doing for so long. we've never, as a community, stood up for ourselves until the white man was involved and then we became outraged. sound familiar? #speakup #metoo #timesup #black #community #support #rkelly #surviving #hushnomore #tired #stop #enough #bgm #blackgirlmonologues #matter #justice #peace #mytruth #unapologetic #strength #tryme #movement #silence

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
tokeativity is turning two today! party with this grassroots group of ladies tonight to celebrate women, and the culture of the cannabis industry! wear anything that reminds you of confetti or inspires you to get your party on. doors open at 7pm at the women friendly center, but don’t forget to register. we are definitely registered to attend events with these fine women!

what is @tokeativity? a global cannabis community for women! they host events each month to offer women a safe space to share, network, and learn about the #cannabisindustry. they also offer classes on cannabis and offer scholarships to low income and minority women.

what will be offered at this event: booths to get your make-up done, headshot photography, craft tables, massage and intuitive reading reiki, and booths by companies in the cannabis industry. very cool space, great people. they definitely offer a very welcoming vibe!

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it. - it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.

when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.'
.
carole cadwalladr
the guardian

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it. - it’s like diy mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.

when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expe for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.'
.
carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
encore troublée, dérangée, pleine d'interrogations sur the scarlet letter d angelica liddell, vu hier soir a @lacollinetheatrenational.

tout y est grand, puissant, provocant - les tableaux, le texte, le jeu poussé aux extrêmes. 
tumulte de références artistiques et symboliques.
le plateau y devient immense. “l'action du théâtre comme celle de la peste est bienfaisante, car poussant les hommes à se voir tels qu'ils sont, elle fait tomber le masque, elle découvre le mensonge, la veulerie, la bassesse, la tartufferie.” dit artaud dans "le théâtre et son double." artaud dont le visage apparaît immense en tableau final du spectacle.

dénonciation des excès de #metoo, par une artiste qui se met en scène comme une reine de la nuit et du mal, domesticant un harem de jeunes éphèbes à son service. 
rien n'est evident dans l'interprétation de ce spectacle. (c)photo: simon gosselin

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

stop sexual violence against black girls! black women matter, but society has proven time and time again that we are less then. society has taken a blind eye to this horrific story aired on lifetime last week of r&b super star r. kelly and the alleged sex cult he maintained for the past 2 decades. you do not have to be a fan of his music to watch the series. after 6 hours of interviews with the women who fell victim to him it is disgusting to think society supported his music for so long. the man can sing but what does that matter when he's using his power to harm black lives? to see the tears from each victims eyes, to hear their stories and do nothing means we fail women of color. would he have been charged with his crimes if the women were caucasian? white privilege is still prevelent in society, and it is time to stop victim blaming. i plead with all women of sexual abuse and violence to watch this. we must stand up for the predators whom seek to deminsh our self worth as women. if you have not seen the 6 part docuseries please take time to watch it and learn about the darkness behind this man whom has brainwashed, abused, manipulated, raped, molested and held girls captive ranging from 12 years old up to women in their 30's, including his own wife. the episodes featured numerous women who described being controlled or abused by the singer, often beginning when they were teenagers. he proudly calls himself the pied piper.... the evidence against this artist is over whelming to say the least and very disturbing. girls are missing, parents are in agony.it is time for women of all color to fight back once and for all. brett cavanaugh was let off the hook. trump was let off the hook all because of their status in society ... how many more women will have their lives ruined before we say no more! when one women suffers we all suffer. there is no peace for one when another is in pain.

text:
how did i do it?

i created this simple system to keep focused on the future and wellness and sobriety 
the outside pentagon represents the five core pillars. i try to do them all everyday but the most important one is no drinking! 
the inside triangle represents mind body and spirit and i try to do something everyday for each of these to stay balanced. 
when i wanted a body transformation i did three things for my body everyday

when i wanted to pay off my debt i did three things for debt payoff everyday

when i wanted to get promoted i used it for my career goals and did three things for my promotion 
it's super flexible and keeps me on track! i don't attend meetings and rarely or never consider drinking anymore because this simple system keeps me so busy! it's hard to do all these everyday! 
it's free and anyone can do it any day at any age. i created it to help myself and my brother from relapsing and to create a healthy and wealthy life
#drydiet #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #empoweringwomen #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #empoweringwomen #addictionrecovery #onedayatatime

text:
想簡單喝杯奶茶都有問題
雖然沒潔癖但僅此於朋友
拿東西給人是甩拍在手上
差點理智線斷掉鬆手回擊
以老鳥姿態說明指揮推責
失笑的覺得新人就是菜味
臨界點的爆炸並不會意外
已經麻痺表面的嘉獎鼓勵
除了快樂健康我別無所求
倒數七開頭我的幸運數字
疲勞轟炸的新年首月崩潰
下班前看著日曆安迪嘆氣
默許自己可以等到歸零天
我會好好完成份內的事情
包含突如其來所交辦的事
除此之外不會有任何私事

絕對不會。

承諾我會為自己負責
我也會因為你們折腰
因為現實就是這樣子
但神話是不會屈服
神創也是

絕對不會。

#shinhwa #신화는꺾이지않아 #metoo

text:
craig mclachlan, has been charged with assault and eight counts of indecent assault relating to events reaching back to 2014 — a potential breakthrough for the media companies he has sued for defamation, and for the country’s nascent #metoo movement.
.
.
.
mr. mclachlan, 53, has been charged for indecent acts said to have occurred in melbourne around the same time as his now-scrutinized performance in a stage version of “the rocky horror show.” his interactions with women during that show’s run at the comedy theater in melbourne were the subject of an investigative report from the sydney morning herald, the age, and abc, australia’s public broadcaster, revealing that several female co-stars accused him of indecent and inappropriate behavior.
.
.
.
the police declined to share specifics of the alleged assaults. however, legal experts said the charges threaten to undermine mr. mclachlan’s defamation claim while highlighting the convoluted nature of australia’s legal system when it comes to sexual assault cases.
.
.
defamation law in australia strongly favors the plaintiff, and it is widely blamed for making it more difficult to confront the problem of sexual harassment.
the powerful men who end up accused tend to sue and the costs can be immense, not just to media companies but also to those who lodge the accusations.
.
.
.
mclachlan is currently suing fairfax media and abc, as well as an actress, christie whelan browne, for 6.5 million australian dollars, about $4.7 million, in damages. still, mclachlan now seems more vulnerable in part, media lawyers say, because the judge in  mclachlan’s case has allowed for a rare defense of “contextual truth.”
.
.
.
4 days after the defamation trial begins on feb. 4, he is scheduled to appear in melbourne magistrates’ court, to face 10 charges brought by the melbourne sexual offenses and child abuse investigation team: one charge of assault, eight charges of indecent assault, and one count of attempted indecent assault.
.
.
#news #australia
